subject:

THIS CHRISTMAS IS CHRIST HAPPY OVER US?
===================================================================
verse:
And now these three remain: faith, hope and love. But the
greatest of these is love.

1 Corinthians 13:13

===================================================================
reflection:

This is a question I am asking myself this year. Let Us All
Give This Question Some Serious Thought! This was a question
a little girl asked her mom. How would you answer this
question? Let us all give this some serious thought. Is the
Lord happy about us on His birthday? Is He really happy,
because He sees within our hearts a deep, true love for Him?
Does He see a satisfying love and not just a seasonal
affection stirred up by the festivities of Christmas?
Remember what He wants more than anything else on His
birthday, IS THE LOVE OF OUR HEARTS.
===================================================================
prayer:

Lord Jesus, as we reflect on Your coming, search our hearts
and deepen our love for You beyond the season’s excitement.
Teach us to honor You not only with songs and gifts, but
with daily obedience, compassion, and devotion. Free us from
shallow affections and form in us a steadfast love that
delights Your heart. May our celebration be the overflow of
lives surrendered to You—today and always. Amen.

===================================================================
